## Step 1: Unit Normalization

**Function**: [extract_normalized_number](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/HPE/HPE-TEAM-6/core/similarity.py#L22-L44)

Before any math, values are converted to **base SI units** so `500mA` and `0.5A` are treated identically:

| Raw Value | Number | Unit | Multiplier | Normalized |
|-----------|--------|------|------------|------------|
| `500mA` | 500 | mA | 1e-3 | **0.5 A** |
| `3.3 V` | 3.3 | V | 1.0 | **3.3 V** |
| `1.2 MHz` | 1.2 | MHz | 1e6 | **1,200,000 Hz** |
| `100µA` | 100 | µA | 1e-6 | **0.0001 A** |
| `47nF` | 47 | nF | 1e-9 | **4.7e-8 F** |

The regex `([-+]?\d*\.?\d+)\s*([a-zA-Z]+)?` extracts the number and unit separately, then looks up the unit in the `UNIT_MULTIPLIERS` dictionary. If no recognized unit is found, the multiplier defaults to `1.0`.

### Supported Unit Families

| Domain | Units (small → large) |
|--------|----------------------|
| Current | nA → µA → mA → A → kA |
| Voltage | µV → mV → V → kV |
| Resistance | mΩ → Ω → kΩ → MΩ |
| Frequency | Hz → kHz → MHz → GHz |
| Power | µW → mW → W → kW |
| Capacitance | pF → nF → µF → mF → F |
| Time | ns → µs → ms → s |

