### What Different Weight Values Mean

| Weight | Behavior |
|---|---|
| **0%** | Feature **completely ignored** — removed from both numerator AND denominator |
| **10% (default)** | Feature has standard importance alongside other default features |
| **30%+** | Feature **dominates** the score — a bad match here tanks the overall % even if everything else matches perfectly |

> [!NOTE]
> The weight is NOT a threshold or filter. Setting Output Current to 30% does NOT mean "only show components with ≥30% match on current." It means "a mismatch on current hurts the overall score 3× more than a mismatch on a default 10% feature."

